===Etymology===
[[File:Icelandic horse1.jpg|thumb|right|250px]]
{{stroke order|type=animate}}
{{liushu|p}}; derived from the pictogram of a horse with its head turned to look back and showing a flowing mane in the wind. The four short strokes at its base ({{m|mul|灬}}) represent its feet, and the sweeping hook stroke in the lower right represents its tail.

Compare also {{m|mul|鳥||bird}}, whose current form is similar (graphically, {{lang|mul|灬}} for claws/legs).

Contrast with {{m|mul|鹿||deer}}, which saw a very different development, and {{m|mul|𢊁||bison}} (as in {{m|mul|薦}}), which is a hybrid: it has the the legs of {{lang|mul|馬}} ({{lang|mul|灬}}) but the head of {{lang|mul|鹿}}.

